import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'])
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Engineers')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between population and number of engineers in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['hurricanes'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='state', y='hurricanes', legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Hurricanes')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of hurricanes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
